TY  - JOUR
AU  - Nickerson, Jordan
T1  - Market Forces and CEO Pay: Shocks to CEO Demand Induced by IPO Waves
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx004
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 7
SP  - 2272
EP  - 2312
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - I develop a simple competitive equilibrium model and derive the prediction that CEO pay-size elasticity increases when more firms compete for an inelastic supply of managers. Using industry-level IPO waves as a proxy for increased competition for CEOs, I find that pay-size elasticity increases by 6% with a one-standard-deviation increase in IPO activity. This effect is stronger in specialized industries. In addition, increased IPO activity leads to a greater likelihood of executive transitions between firms. These findings indicate that market forces play a key role in the determination of CEO pay.Received August 6, 2015; editorial decision September 24, 2016 by Editor Francesca Cornelli.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx004
ER  - 



